  {
    "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#BronzeLayer",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#Class"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "The Bronze layer of the Semantic Medallion where raw data is harvested from source systems — no semantics, just raw material."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#semanticMedallionOntology"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Bronze Layer"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#MedallionLayer"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#layerOrder",
    "@type": [
      "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#Property"
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "The ordinal position of a medallion layer in the pipeline (1=Bronze, 2=Silver, 3=Gold)."
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain": [
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#MedallionLayer"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#isDefinedBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#semanticMedallionOntology"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "layer order"
      }
    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range": [
      {
        "@id": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#step2",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/HowToStep"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/isPartOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#howtoSection"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Step 2: Mint Stable IRIs at the Silver Layer"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/position": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer",
        "@value": 2
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "For every entity in the Bronze data, create a stable globally unique IRI. Choose a consistent IRI pattern (e.g., https://company.example/entity/{type}/{id}). Store the IRI-to-record mapping. This is the most critical step — IRIs are the foundation for all downstream linking."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#a11",
    "@type": [
      "http://schema.org/Answer"
    ],
    "http://schema.org/isPartOf": [
      {
        "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#faqSection"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/text": [
      {
        "@language": "en",
        "@value": "Three key lessons: (1) Start with IRIs early — minting identifiers at the Silver layer pays compounding dividends as more systems connect. (2) Design ontologies iteratively — begin with a minimal shared ontology and expand as new use cases emerge rather than attempting a complete model upfront. (3) The medallion is about semantic enrichment layers — Bronze has no semantics, Silver has local semantics, Gold has global semantics. Each layer adds meaning rather than just cleanliness."
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://moderndata101.substack.com/p/the-semantic-medallion#bronzeSection",
